This is simple project which accept directory name and read that directory if regular file having size more than 1kb it truncate that file to 1kb and if file size is less than 1kb it creates holes in between that file.Name of directory should be given as command line argument.This project use make commands to build and execute.Use <make> or <make build> commad to build the project.Use <make help> for help and more details about how to give commands and execute the project. 
